snippet: Saboteurs blew up a pipeline in Egypt that supplied gas to Israel, the 12th such attack in a year, security officials said.
abstract: Egyptian security officials report the sabotage of a pipeline supplying natural gas to Israel, the 12th such attack in a year; first attack occurred during the mass uprisings that drove Pres Hosni Mubarak from power.
lead_paragraph: Saboteurs blew up a pipeline in Egypt that supplied gas to Israel, the 12th such attack in a year, security officials said.

headline.seo: Egyptian Pipeline Supplying Israel Is Attacked
